        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3183364227" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9101260078595329431">I was sorry to finish this one as it was Hillerman&apos;s final Leaphorn &amp; Chee novel. I think he may have known he was nearing the end because it is much better put together than some of his later works like &quot;The Sinister Pig&quot;. The book is much more focused on Leaphorn as well. While I like Bernie &amp; Chee, it seems like Leaphorn is a more developed and thoughtful character. He wanted it to end with a strong finish if you will. It seems obvious to me that Hillerman liked his Leaphorn character and tha</span>
  <span id="freeText9101260078595329431" style="display:none">I was sorry to finish this one as it was Hillerman's final Leaphorn &amp; Chee novel. I think he may have known he was nearing the end because it is much better put together than some of his later works like "The Sinister Pig". The book is much more focused on Leaphorn as well. While I like Bernie &amp; Chee, it seems like Leaphorn is a more developed and thoughtful character. He wanted it to end with a strong finish if you will. It seems obvious to me that Hillerman liked his Leaphorn character and that Leaphorn's retirement was mirroring his own life. <br /><br />Interestingly, there is no real mystery as to the killer quite early in the book. Ordinarily, this would be a problem, but in this case, I was happy to follow the methodical search. <br /><br />Again, I would not start with this effort if you are unfamiliar with the characters. Start with "The Blessing Way"; "Skinwalkers"; or "Sacred Clowns" instead. A fitting farewell story to a remarkable series of books. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9101260078595329431" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

